{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":138294,"duration_api_ms":125228,"num_turns":2,"result":"## Ingestion Module in `core_business_v2`\n\n### Location\n`/Users/zliu/IdeaProjects/FortiNAC/core_business_v2/ingestion`\n\n### Package Structure\n- `controller/` — REST endpoints\n- `consumer/` — Redis stream consumers + state machine + orchestrator + handlers\n- `service/stages/` — Business logic per processing stage\n- `entity/` — JPA entities\n- `repository/` — DB access\n- `dto/` — Data transfer objects\n- `registry/` — Callback and processing registries\n- `config/`, `util/`, `job/`, `delayqueue/`\n\n---\n\n### REST Endpoints\n\n| Controller | Path | Method | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **IngestionController** | `POST /api/v1/ingestion/events` | `ingestEvent()` | Main entry — publishes to Redis stream, registers callback with 60s timeout, returns result reactively |\n| | `GET /api/v1/ingestion/health-check` | | Health probe |\n| **EntityController** | `POST /api/v1/entities/query` | `queryFailedEntities()` | Query entities with filtering/pagination |\n| | `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}` | | Get entity by ID |\n| | `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` | | Display status (init/running/enforced/failed) |\n| **PolicyController** | `POST /api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` | `applyExistingEntities()` | Mark all entities for reprocessing |\n| **FingerprintController** | `POST /api/v1/fingerprint/calculate` | `calc()` | Compute attribute fingerprint |\n\n---\n\n### State Machine (`EntityStateMachine`)\n\nFour stages driven by `EntityStage` enum:\n\n```\nPENDING  →  LABELED  →  EVALUATED  →  ENFORCED\n   │            │            │\n   ▼            ▼            ▼\nLabelService  PolicyService  EnforcementService\n```\n\nEach stage:\n- Wrapped in `@Transactional` via `EntityStageTransactionRunner`\n- Up to **3 retries** with exponential backoff + jitter (1s × attempt + random 0–99ms)\n- Error codes determine retryability: `21xx`/`31xx`/`41xx` = retryable, `22xx`/`32xx`/`42xx` = permanent failure\n- DB state updated after each stage completes\n\n---\n\n### End-to-End Request Flow\n\n```\nREST POST /api/v1/ingestion/events\n    │\n    ▼\nIngestionController\n    ├── Register CompletableFuture in IngestionCallbackRegistry\n    └── Publish to Redis INGESTION_INTERNAL_STREAM\n            │\n            ▼\nIngestionInternalConsumer (Redis stream listener)\n            │\n            ▼\nIngestionOrchestrator.process()\n    ├── Cache lookup (Redis) → hit? → CachedExistingEntityHandler\n    ├── Miss → acquire distributed create lock\n    │       ├── Lock acquired → DB lookup\n    │       │     ├── Found → DbExistingEntityHandler\n    │       │     └── Not found → NewEntityHandler\n    │       └── Lock not acquired → requeue with backoff (2s,4s,8s,16s,32s; max 5)\n    │\n    ▼\nHandler (New or Existing)\n    ├── Validate referenced entities (Host/Adapter/User)\n    ├── Create/update Entity in DB (state = PENDING)\n    ├── Cache entity ID in Redis\n    ├── Acquire distributed process lock\n    └── Start EntityStateMachine.start()\n            │\n            ▼\n        PENDING → LabelService.label()   → LABELED\n        LABELED → PolicyService.evaluate() → EVALUATED\n        EVALUATED → EnforcementService.enforce() → ENFORCED\n            │\n            ▼\n        IngestionCallbackRegistry.complete(requestId, result)\n            │\n            ▼\n        CompletableFuture resolves → REST response returned\n```\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n- **Distributed locking** (Redis): separate create-lock and process-lock prevent duplicate entity creation and concurrent state machine execution\n- **Attribute fingerprinting**: deduplicates identical requests; `FingerprintCase` enum determines behavior based on fingerprint match × lock status (SAME_ATTR_LOCK, DIFF_ATTR_LOCK, etc.)\n- **Callback registry**: `CompletableFuture`-based with timeout auto-cleanup — bridges async Redis consumer back to synchronous REST response\n- **Transaction isolation**: each stage runs in its own `@Transactional`; state updates use `REQUIRES_NEW` propagation so they commit even if the outer tx fails\n- **External → Internal queue**: `IngestionExternalConsumer` validates and forwards to internal stream, separating ingress concerns from business logic","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"37806ae7-e1d6-4c66-a775-97d18fe8515c","total_cost_usd":0.4727154,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19187,"cache_read_input_tokens":36931,"output_tokens":1579,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":19187,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1579,"cacheReadInputTokens":36931,"cacheCreationInputTokens":19187,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.17787925,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":96,"outputTokens":8028,"cacheReadInputTokens":1358014,"cacheCreationInputTokens":95039,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.29483614999999996,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"707ae7f2-98fe-45b9-aa79-87f04605ddf3"}
